==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ri:m/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːm|-iːm]]

===Etymology 1===
Old English ''rēam''.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{italbrac|obsolete except in dialects}} the [[cream]] of milk
# {{italbrac|obsolete except in dialects}} a [[froth]] or [[scum]]

===Etymology 2===
From {{etymon|fro|raime}} (French [[rame]]), from Arabic [[رزمة]] ''rizma'' ‘bundle’.

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A bundle, package, or quantity of paper, usually containing 500 sheets 
# an abstract large amount of something
#:''I can't go - I still have '''reams''' of work left.''

===Etymology 3===
Unknown origin.

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# to enlarge a hole, especially using a [[reamer]]; to [[bore]] a hole wider.
# to shape or form, especially using a [[reamer]].
# to remove (material) by [[reaming]].
# (''Slang'') to yell at or berate.
# (''Slang'') [[anilingus]]

